Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA (EEB) ,
 Colombia â€™s second-biggest electricity distributor, will offer to
sell up to 1 trillion pesos of shares ($512 million) in local
market starting today.  EEB, as the company is known, will offer to sell 538.5
million shares at 1,300 pesos each and raise the offer to 769.2
million shares if there is sufficient demand, it said in a
statement published today in La Republica newspaper. The offer
runs through Oct. 27, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
